# Ventium SoC peripheral placement — where each device lives:
#   rtl = synthesized into the PL fabric (a ven_* RTL module in ventium_soc)
#   ps  = run as a C model on the PS A53 (the SoC forwards that port range over the
#         AXI-Lite io-bridge; ven_soc_axil + sw/ps_periph/<dev>.c service it)
#
# This is the fabric-fit knob: the KV260 PL is routing/congestion-bound, so push the
# SLOW peripherals onto the A53 and keep only the BUS-CRITICAL ones in PL. Run
#   python3 fpga/scripts/gen_periph_split.py
# to regenerate rtl/soc/ven_periph_split.svh (the +define gating) and the TB/PS
# C dispatch table (verif/tb/ps_periph_table.inc) from this file.
#
# Each `ps` device must have a matching C model in sw/ps_periph/<dev>.c, verified
# bit-exact vs qemu by run-soc-<dev>-gate.sh built with +VEN_<DEV>_PS (the device
# is then served by its C model instead of the RTL module).
#
#   device   placement   notes
# ---------- ---------   ----------------------------------------------------------
# BUS-CRITICAL — keep in PL (low INTR/INTA latency, address-bus / DMA gating):
pic          rtl         # 8259 PIC      — INTR/INTA latency
pit          rtl         # 8254 PIT      — IRQ0 timebase
port92       rtl         # fast A20      — gates the address bus
ide          rtl         # IDE/ATA       — bus-master DMA path
dma          rtl         # 8237 ctrl0    — bus master
dma2         rtl         # 8237 ctrl1    — bus master
# SLOW — default to PS (A53 C model), freeing PL fabric. Each has a verified C model
# in sw/ps_periph/ (run-soc-ps-cosim-gate.sh <dev> -> per-record EQUIVALENT vs qemu).
# Flip any back to `rtl` to synthesize it into the PL instead.
rtc          ps          # MC146818 RTC  -> ven_rtc.c       (cosim EQUIVALENT)
i8042        ps          # 8042 kbd/mouse-> ven_i8042.c     (cosim EQUIVALENT; A20 gate -> PS path on board)
vga          ps          # VGA registers -> ven_vgaregs.c   (cosim EQUIVALENT; mode bits -> PS path on board)
acpipm       ps          # ACPI PM timer -> ven_acpipm.c    (cosim EQUIVALENT)
uart         ps          # 16550 COM1    -> ven_uart16550.c (cosim EQUIVALENT)
fdc          ps          # 82077 floppy  -> ven_i8272.c     (cosim EQUIVALENT)
